  sectionEyebrow="What drift looks like"
  sectionH2="A drop that would have stayed invisible until the next review."
  sectionBody="A claims-triage bot served twelve policyholders a subtly wrong coverage interpretation the morning after a provider updated their model. Phidea's probes caught it within the hour. The alert was paged to AI-ops; the gateway switched to observe-only on that agent; the vendor ticket was open before lunch. Between-audit drift is the entire reason the platform exists."
  faqs={[
    { q: "Which probes detect drift?", a: "Grounding score, policy-adherence rate, refusal rate, hallucination-classifier score, per-persona behavior. Thresholds are baselined per agent." },
    { q: "Does it detect vendor-side prompt changes?", a: "Yes — via behavioral fingerprinting. We don't need the vendor to announce a change." },
    { q: "How false-positive heavy is it?", a: "Baselines are per-agent, per-LOB. Expect one paged alert per month per agent in steady state." },
  ]}
  ctaH2="Request a drift demo."
